<reggrp_short_dscr>:
AFI Table UPdata Engine (AFI TUPE)
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
Engine - called "AFI TUPE" - for updating TTI Table.

TUPE is used as follows:
1) Configure TUPE parameters.
2) Set TUPE_MISC.TUPE_START=1
3) Await TUPE_MISC.TUPE_START=0

While TUPE is running (i.e. TUPE_START=1) CPU must not write to TTI Table.
While TUPE is running no injections will be performed for TTIs within configured TUPE address range and matching the configured TUPE criteria.
